Overview
This repository contains my notes and learnings from the Network Fundamentals module on TryHackMe. The goal is to document the essential concepts of computer networks and their importance in cybersecurity.

🔑 Key Topics Covered
What is Networking? – Basics of how computers communicate.

LANs – Local Area Networks and their technologies.

OSI Model – The 7 layers and their role in data transmission.

Packets & Frames – How data is divided and transmitted across networks.

Expanding Networks – Technologies and motivations for scaling networks.

🎯 Why It Matters
Understanding these fundamentals is crucial for identifying vulnerabilities and securing systems. Networking knowledge is the backbone of cybersecurity.

